
Overview of verb crumble

The verb crumble has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (2) crumble, crumple, tumble, break down, collapse -- (fall apart; "the building crumbled after the explosion"; "Negotiations broke down")
2. crumble, fall apart -- (break or fall apart into fragments; "The cookies crumbled"; "The Sphinx is crumbling")
3. decay, crumble, dilapidate -- (fall into decay or ruin; "The unoccupied house started to decay")
